snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Sajjad, I am writing this from the very bottom of my heart, and could like to congratulate you and the entire team of coke studio especially Rohail for touching numerous lives around the world through COKE Studio. You guys are amazing and your work is highly commendable. Coming to this song,  I live in Canada but every time I hear this song it brings me it tears, and drive me home (Pakistan) right away. Everything about this song is incredible, I am a musician myself, and I believe song as a whole that touches your heart and soul and speaks to you so intimately could be something divine and not from this world. 
Sajjad thank you for putting your heart and soul into this song, apart from the that this would have been meaningless. I personally believe and pray that this song has and may heal many broken lives and families around the globe especially relationships that are on the verge of falling apart. Blessings to you all who worked so diligently in carving and polishing this wonderful piece of music jewel. Warmly, ELI (Alberta, Canada)

snippet.textDisplay: Before season 7 it was mesmerizing to watch CS Pakistan videos instead of the modern day Hollywood/Bollywood foolish dancing/singing that to me is mostly disgusting show business and undermines real singing and music. CS Pakistan had revived the real singing and the musical instruments and talents from all over the world to create an orchestra under Rohail Hyat to match the folk and sufi singing. It was just revolutionary and great achievement.
